<item>
            <title>[LU-7682] Interop 2.7.1&lt;-&gt;master - sanity-benchmark: no subtests ran</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7682</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Saurabh Tandan &amp;lt;saurabh.tandan@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
sanity-benchmark failed with the following issue in suite_log:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Setup mgs, mdt, osts
CMD: shadow-35vm3 mkdir -p /mnt/mds1
CMD: shadow-35vm3 test -b /dev/lvm-Role_MDS/P1
Starting mds1:   /dev/lvm-Role_MDS/P1 /mnt/mds1
CMD: shadow-35vm3 mkdir -p /mnt/mds1; mount -t lustre   		                   /dev/lvm-Role_MDS/P1 /mnt/mds1
shadow-35vm3: mount.lustre: according to /etc/mtab /dev/mapper/lvm--Role_MDS-P1 is already mounted on /mnt/mds1
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue has been seen around 18 times in past 30 days.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/607eb636-bac4-11e5-9137-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/607eb636-bac4-11e5-9137-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Might be related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6248&quot; title=&quot;sanity-scrub: Failed mount OST&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6248&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6248&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Interop: Server: master, build# 3303, RHEL 7&lt;br/&gt;
Client: 2.7.1, b2_7_fe/34&lt;br/&gt;
Also impacts master patch testing in autotest</environment>
