                            <comment id="140208" author="jamesanunez" created="Wed, 27 Jan 2016 15:44:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We see this happen frequently in master patch testing, meaning in testing other than interop, where a test suite fails and then the next test suite does not run any tests because a MDT is already mounted. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the examples below, sanity-sec, insanity, replay-ost-single, ost-pools, and sanity-hsm fail due to the mdt being mounted when the test suite starts running:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2016-01-26 - &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/055b35b4-c46e-11e5-a651-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/055b35b4-c46e-11e5-a651-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
2016-02-17 - &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/fd51ce20-d546-11e5-9cc2-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/fd51ce20-d546-11e5-9cc2-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
2016-02-21 - &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/a9d0887c-d8de-11e5-b4e5-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/a9d0887c-d8de-11e5-b4e5-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
